.\" hsh - holberton simple_shell
.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "holbertonschool-simple_shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- small UNIX command-line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.PP
The string you used to launch the program (e.g.
.BR ./hsh )
is what shows up as
.BR argv[0]
in error messages.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is the Holberton
.B simple_shell
assignement boiled down to something that actualy runs: read a line with
.BR getline (3),
split it into words, then either handle a built-in in the parent or
.BR fork (2)
and
.BR execve (2)
in a child. The environment you started with is what we pass through; nothing magic.
.PP
Interactive sessions (stdin is a tty) print
.B "($) "
before each read. Piped or scripted input gets no prompt. End of file on stdin exits the shell; in interactive mode we print a newline first so the termnal does not look stuck.
.PP
Commands without a slash in the name are looked up using
.BR PATH .
Full paths run as-is when the file is executable. Unknown commands print
.BI argv0 ": " line ": " command ": not found"
to stderr, with a line counter that starts at 1 and ticks every time we accept a line (built-ins and empty parses still advance it when we loop).
.PP
How to compile and which flags the school wants are in
.B README.md
at the repo root; this page is just how the binary behaves once built.
.SH "BUILT-IN COMMANDS"
.TP
.BR exit
Leave
.B hsh .
We do not need to handle arguments to
.B exit
for this project version.
.TP
.BR env
Dump the current
.B enviroment
(one
.B name=value
per line, same order we walk the pointer array).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
Inherited from the parent. Child processes get the same map through
.BR execve .
.B PATH
drives where we search for bare command names.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
0 when the read loop ends normally, inlcuding EOF on stdin.
.B exit
also stops the shell with status 0 here.
.SH BUGS
No pipes, no redirection, no real quoting, no
.BR cd .
Do not expect POSIX
.BR sh
compat; this is a class exercise, not a daily driver.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.B README.md
for build notes and where the sources live;
.B AUTHORS
for who touched the repo.
